ORAL SCREENING CAMP

Body:
b'     Dear All,     We wish to have a dedicated oral health day on 29032016.   Screening is for staff, their dependents,, students and their families and nonentitled.   Oral cancerous lesions are prevalent in smokers, tobacco or hans users, ethanolics and people with sharp teeth.  Lips, tongue, gums , floor and roof of the buccal cavity are most likely to be affected. Individuals with or without any lesions can attend the screening camp. Those with family history of oral cancer kindly screen yourselves .  Individuals with the following lesions must attend the screening camp: any form of lesion or small growth, Leukoplakia (white patch), Erythroplakia ( red patch ), Erythroleukoplakia ( red and white patches), sharp teeth and Velvetty patches.  Screening Done by   Dr D. Sankar M.D.S (Oral MaxilloFacial Surgeon)  Venue : Institute Hospital Date : 29032016 Time : 9.30 am to 1.30 pm       Kindly register either through online or duty room  8331.      Kindly spread the message.    Registerhere        with regards,  Dr. Mahalakshmi '

